projects.description:
Technical Lead for delivering an upgrade to one of Stageclip's core video creation and processing services by transitioning to using Adobe After Effects. This will:
* Enable the customer to improve the quality of their core product (professionally customised videos);
* Create a new UI for the content team to use the new service, improving the process and experience of creating and managing content.

In this role, I am responsible for:
* Ensuring other developers have the technical knowledge, capability and support to complete their tasks;
* Gathering requirements and refining the technical specification;
* Providing regular updates to the Stageclip CTO, informing them of progress, risks and actions;
* Working closely with the project manager, customer manager, and Stageclip in-house engineering team to ensure timely and effective delivery;
* Exploring opportunities for new work;
* Overseeing code reviews;
* Developing the frontend UI.

Worked across a range of products to accelerate David Lloyd's digital transformation roadmap. Their plan was split across workstreams to increase new membership, improve retention, increase sales & subscriptions (e.g. to classes and courses) and streamline their internal processes to improve efficiency.

My role included work to:
* Upgrade their public facing website to increase membership sign-ups by providing a modern design and customisable content via a custom-made Content Management System;
* Upgrade their internal booking system to automate manual processes and improving the code base by extracting an old PHP monolith into Java microservices;
* Create a new membership registration app for in-club sales teams to improve the registration process and experience for both staff and prospective members.
